    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'm using nvim with clangd-19. It loads correctly, does syntax highlighting, then stops working until I restart nvim. The following is seen in the LSP log:\n\n```\n[ERROR][2025-07-11 14:58:34] ...p/_transport.lua:36     \"rpc\"   \"clangd\"        \"stderr\"        \"I[14:58:34.977] --> reply:textDocument/semanticTokens/full(2) 10 ms, error: Task was cancelled.\\n\"\n[ERROR][2025-07-11 14:58:34] ...p/_transport.lua:36     \"rpc\"   \"clangd\"        \"stderr\"        \"I[14:58:34.977] --> reply:textDocument/semanticTokens/full(3) 6 ms\\n\"\n[ERROR][2025-07-11 14:58:35] ...p/_transport.lua:36     \"rpc\"   \"clangd\"        \"stderr\"        \"I[14:58:35.592] Indexed c++17 standard library (incomplete due to errors): 14136 symbols, 1812 filtered\\n\"\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nUsed minimal config and project as seen at https://gist.github.com/xim/ca4951715d15591a5a5f11937c0a219e\n\nStarting nvim using\n```sh\nnvim --clean -u min.lua test.cpp\n```\n\nWhen I change the file, the diagnostics etc don't update.\n\nOther details:\n`gcc 14.2.0-4ubuntu2~24.04` is the system default C compiler\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected it to update.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.2\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nclangd version 19.1.1 (1ubuntu1~24.04.2)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04.2 LTS\n\n### Log file\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/xim/ca4951715d15591a5a5f11937c0a219e",
